5d8ad0a2-c35e-456f-8e06-3448ddc015a8.do_description: To make the output, you have to...use the color blue to extend a 1x1 length of pixels northwest of the 2x2 blue box until there is no more room left. Then extend a 1x1 length of pixels southeast from the 2x2 red box until there is no more room left.
5d8ad0a2-c35e-456f-8e06-3448ddc015a8.grid_description: The output grid size...same as the input size
5d8ad0a2-c35e-456f-8e06-3448ddc015a8.see_description: In the input, you should see...two 2x2 boxes, one red and one blue

71a6ccf5-b207-4e4d-8c60-e0dde462b557.do_description: To make the output, you have to...create a single line of boxes matching the color of the 2x2 box. Begin with the top left corner of the blue and the bottom right of the red and go out to the edge of the grid.
71a6ccf5-b207-4e4d-8c60-e0dde462b557.grid_description: The output grid size...same as input
71a6ccf5-b207-4e4d-8c60-e0dde462b557.see_description: In the input, you should see...two boxes, one red and one blue, that are 2x2

b9e63bdf-8226-4083-8310-2de4e8490833.do_description: To make the output, you have to...add blue squares to the blue box diagonally from the top left until it reaches the side. For the red box, you have to add red squares from the bottom right box until it reaches the side.
b9e63bdf-8226-4083-8310-2de4e8490833.grid_description: The output grid size...is the same as the input
b9e63bdf-8226-4083-8310-2de4e8490833.see_description: In the input, you should see...two boxes, one red and one blue
